# Project Structure

This is a Next.js project with TypeScript. The main project structure is organized as follows:

## Web Directory
The `web` directory contains the main Next.js application:

- [package.json](mdc:web/package.json) - Project configurations and dependencies
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:web/tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configurations
- [next.config.ts](mdc:web/next.config.ts) - Next.js configurations
- [app/](mdc:web/app) - Main application directory (routes and components)
- [public/](mdc:web/public) - Static files

## Documentation
- [docs/](mdc:docs) - Project documentation

## Code Conventions
1. We use TypeScript for all code
2. React components should be functional and use hooks
3. We follow Next.js 14+ App Router conventions
4. We use ESLint to maintain code quality

